headline: Payments processor FIS forecasts third-quarter profit below estimates
summary: Banking and payments processing firm Fidelity National Information Services forecast third-quarter profit below Wall Street estimates on Tuesday, amid concerns of dampened consumer spending. Consumers continue to spend on essentials while cutting back on discretionary items, as economic uncertainty from geopolitical tensions and President Donald Trump's trade policies persists. Lower spending volumes could hurt payment processors such as FIS that collect transaction fees from financial institutions and businesses.
